---
import GeminiLayout from "../../layouts/GeminiLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/cheatsheet-shared.css";
---

<GeminiLayout
  title="Gemini CLI Tips & Tricks — changelogs.info"
  description="Quick wins, hidden features, common mistakes, and workflow combos for Gemini CLI."
  currentPage="tips"
>
  <div class="cs-wrapper">

    <section class="cs-hero">
      <div class="cs-hero__emoji">💡</div>
      <h1 class="gc-headline cs-hero__title">
        Tips &<span class="cs-hero__accent"> Tricks</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="cs-hero__sub">Quick wins, hidden features, and the mistakes everyone makes once.</p>
    </section>

    <div class="cs-grid">

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="gc-headline cs-panel__title">Quick Wins</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Use -p for one-shot mode</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> gemini -p "summarize this repo"</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Non-interactive one-shot mode — perfect for scripts and automation.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">--yolo skips confirmations</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Skips all confirmation prompts for the session. Use carefully — it's sticky for the entire session.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Feed it the whole codebase</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">1M context window means you can give Gemini your entire codebase. Don't hold back — more context = better results.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Set default model in profile</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> export GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-pro</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Add to your shell profile to avoid typing <code>--model</code> every time.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Pipe files via stdin</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> cat bigfile.ts | gemini -p "review for security issues"</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Feed any file directly into Gemini for focused analysis.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--accent">
        <h2 class="gc-headline cs-panel__title">Hidden Features</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Checkpointing</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Use <code>--checkpoint</code> on long tasks so you can resume if interrupted. Essential for tasks over 5 minutes.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">gVisor sandbox</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc"><code>--sandbox</code> runs shell commands inside gVisor isolation — safer for untrusted or exploratory code.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item cs-item--accent">
            <div class="cs-item__title cs-item__title--accent">Policy engine</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Pre-approve certain action types to skip confirmations selectively, without going full --yolo.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel cs-panel--warning">
        <h2 class="gc-headline cs-panel__title">Common Mistakes</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Forgetting --yolo is sticky</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Once enabled, --yolo stays on for the whole session. If you didn't mean to skip all confirmations, start a new session.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Browser auth in scripts</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Browser auth doesn't work in CI/automation. Set <code>GEMINI_API_KEY</code> instead.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Giving small context</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">You have 1M tokens of context — use it. Giving Gemini only one file when you could give the whole repo leaves performance on the table.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cs-panel">
        <h2 class="gc-headline cs-panel__title">Workflow Combos</h2>
        <div class="cs-item-list">
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Full-repo security audit</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> gemini -p "audit this entire codebase for OWASP top 10 vulnerabilities"</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Feed the whole repo into the 1M context window for a comprehensive security review.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-item">
            <div class="cs-item__title">Safe exploration of untrusted code</div>
            <div class="cs-item__cmd"><span class="cs-step-cmd__prompt">$</span> gemini --sandbox --checkpoint</div>
            <p class="cs-item__desc">Combine gVisor isolation with checkpointing for safe, resumable exploration.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</GeminiLayout>
